TITLE: Implementing Dapr Workflow in Python
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a workflow function using Python's DaprWorkflowContext. Includes activity calls, child workflow execution, event handling with timeout, and retry policy implementation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/developing-applications/building-blocks/workflow/howto-author-workflow.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
@wfr.workflow(name='hello_world_wf')
def hello_world_wf(ctx: DaprWorkflowContext, wf_input):
    print(f'{wf_input}')
    yield ctx.call_activity(hello_act, input=1)
    yield ctx.call_activity(hello_act, input=10)
    yield ctx.call_activity(hello_retryable_act, retry_policy=retry_policy)
    yield ctx.call_child_workflow(child_retryable_wf, retry_policy=retry_policy)

    # Change in event handling: Use when_any to handle both event and timeout
    event = ctx.wait_for_external_event(event_name)
    timeout = ctx.create_timer(timedelta(seconds=30))
    winner = yield when_any([event, timeout])

    if winner == timeout:
        print('Workflow timed out waiting for event')
        return 'Timeout'

    yield ctx.call_activity(hello_act, input=100)
    yield ctx.call_activity(hello_act, input=1000)
    return 'Completed'
```

