TITLE: Configuring JWKS Component in Dapr's crypto.yaml
DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration demonstrates how to set up the JWKS component in Dapr. It includes examples of loading JWKS from a file, a URL, and directly in the configuration. The component supports automatic reloading for file-based JWKS and periodic refreshing for URL-based JWKS.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/reference/components-reference/supported-cryptography/json-web-key-sets.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
apiVersion: dapr.io/v1alpha1
kind: Component
metadata:
  name: jwks
spec:
  type: crypto.dapr.jwks
  version: v1
  metadata:
    # Example 1: load JWKS from file
    - name: "jwks"
      value: "fixtures/crypto/jwks/jwks.json"
    # Example 2: load JWKS from a HTTP(S) URL
    # Only "jwks" is required
    - name: "jwks"
      value: "https://example.com/.well-known/jwks.json"
    - name: "requestTimeout"
      value: "30s"
    - name: "minRefreshInterval"
      value: "10m"
    # Option 3: include the actual JWKS
    - name: "jwks"
      value: |
        {
          "keys": [
            {
              "kty": "RSA",
              "use": "sig",
              "kid": "",
              "n": "",
              "e": "",
              "issuer": "https://example.com"
            }
          ]
        }
    # Option 3b: include the JWKS base64-encoded
    - name: "jwks"
      value: |
        eyJrZXlzIjpbeyJ
```

