TITLE: Publishing Event with TTL using Dapr Python SDK
DESCRIPTION: This Python code snippet shows how to publish an event to 'TOPIC_A' with a TTL of 120 seconds using the Dapr Python SDK. It creates a DaprClient and uses the publish_event method to send the message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/developing-applications/building-blocks/pubsub/pubsub-message-ttl.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from dapr.clients import DaprClient

with DaprClient() as d:
    req_data = {
        'order-number': '345'
    }
    # Create a typed message with content type and body
    resp = d.publish_event(
        pubsub_name='pubsub',
        topic='TOPIC_A',
        data=json.dumps(req_data),
        publish_metadata={'ttlInSeconds': '120'}
    )
    # Print the request
    print(req_data, flush=True)
```

