TITLE: PostgreSQL Notification Trigger Function
DESCRIPTION: PL/pgSQL function that creates a notification trigger for configuration changes, converting row data to JSON and broadcasting events.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/reference/components-reference/supported-configuration-stores/postgresql-configuration-store.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION notify_event() RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
    DECLARE 
        data json;
        notification json;

    BEGIN

        IF (TG_OP = 'DELETE') THEN
            data = row_to_json(OLD);
        ELSE
            data = row_to_json(NEW);
        END IF;

        notification = json_build_object(
                          'table',TG_TABLE_NAME,
                          'action', TG_OP,
                          'data', data);
        PERFORM pg_notify('config',notification::text);
        RETURN NULL; 
    END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;
```

