TITLE: Configuring Node.js App Access Control in Dapr (YAML)
DESCRIPTION: YAML configuration for the Node.js app that denies access to the 'neworder' method from the Python app. Sets a trust domain of 'public' with specific deny rules for the Python app in the 'myDomain' trust domain.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/operations/configuration/invoke-allowlist.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
apiVersion: dapr.io/v1alpha1
kind: Configuration
metadata:
  name: nodeappconfig
spec:
  tracing:
    samplingRate: "1"
  accessControl:
    defaultAction: allow
    trustDomain: "public"
    policies:
    - appId: pythonapp
      defaultAction: allow
      trustDomain: 'myDomain'
      namespace: "default"
      operations:
      - name: /neworder
        httpVerb: ['POST']
        action: deny
```

