TITLE: Parameterized SQL Query Examples
DESCRIPTION: These SQL snippets illustrate the difference between a vulnerable query prone to SQL injection and a secure parameterized query. The secure version uses a placeholder ($1) for user input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/reference/components-reference/supported-bindings/postgresql.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
--  WRONG! Includes values in the query and is vulnerable to SQL Injection attacks.
SELECT * FROM mytable WHERE user_key = 'something';

--  GOOD! Uses parametrized queries.
-- This will be executed with parameters ["something"]
SELECT * FROM mytable WHERE user_key = $1;
```

