TITLE: Programmatic Subscription to Raw Messages in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example of programmatically subscribing to raw pub/sub messages in PHP by setting the rawPayload metadata flag to true in the subscription configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/developing-applications/building-blocks/pubsub/pubsub-raw.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

require_once __DIR__.'/vendor/autoload.php';

$app = \Dapr\App::create(configure: fn(\DI\ContainerBuilder $builder) => $builder->addDefinitions(['dapr.subscriptions' => [
    new \Dapr\PubSub\Subscription(pubsubname: 'pubsub', topic: 'deathStarStatus', route: '/dsstatus', metadata: [ 'rawPayload' => 'true'] ),
]]));

$app->post('/dsstatus', function(
    #[\Dapr\Attributes\FromBody]
    \Dapr\PubSub\CloudEvent $cloudEvent,
    \Psr\Log\LoggerInterface $logger
    ) {
        $logger->alert('Received event: {event}', ['event' => $cloudEvent]);
        return ['status' => 'SUCCESS'];
    }
);

$app->start();
```

