TITLE: Configuring Kafka with TLS Communication
DESCRIPTION: YAML configuration for Kafka pubsub component with TLS transport security. Includes CA certificate configuration and basic connection settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/reference/components-reference/supported-pubsub/setup-apache-kafka.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
apiVersion: dapr.io/v1alpha1
kind: Component
metadata:
  name: kafka-pubsub
spec:
  type: pubsub.kafka
  version: v1
  metadata:
  - name: brokers
    value: "dapr-kafka.myapp.svc.cluster.local:9092"
  - name: consumerGroup
    value: "group1"
  - name: clientID
    value: "my-dapr-app-id"
  - name: authType
    value: "certificate"
  - name: consumeRetryInterval
    value: 200ms
  - name: heartbeatInterval
    value: 5s
  - name: sessionTimeout
    value: 15s
  - name: version
    value: 0.10.2.0
  - name: maxMessageBytes
    value: 1024
  - name: caCert
    secretKeyRef:
      name: kafka-tls
      key: caCert
auth:
  secretStore: <SECRET_STORE_NAME>
```

