TITLE: Deploying Linux Application with Node Affinity
DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration defines a Kubernetes Deployment for a Linux application. It includes Dapr annotations and node affinity rules to ensure the application is scheduled on Linux nodes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/operations/hosting/kubernetes/kubernetes-hybrid-clusters.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: yourlinuxapp
  labels:
    app: yourlabel
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: yourlabel
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: yourlabel
      annotations:
        dapr.io/enabled: "true"
        dapr.io/id: "addapp"
        dapr.io/port: "6000"
        dapr.io/config: "appconfig"
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: add
        image: yourreponsitory/your-application:your-tag
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6000
        imagePullPolicy: Always
      affinity:
        nodeAffinity:
          requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
            nodeSelectorTerms:
              - matchExpressions:
                - key: kubernetes.io/os
                  operator: In
                  values:
                  - linux
```

