TITLE: Creating Index for Expiration Date in PostgreSQL State Table
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query creates an index on the 'expiredate' column in the 'state' table to optimize the cleanup process for TTL records. This is useful for tables with a large number of records where only some use TTL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/reference/components-reference/supported-state-stores/setup-postgresql-v1.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
CREATE INDEX expiredate_idx
    ON state
    USING btree (expiredate ASC NULLS LAST);
```

