TITLE: Setting State with TTL Using Curl
DESCRIPTION: Example of setting state with a Time To Live (TTL) value of 120 seconds using curl.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dapr/docs/blob/v1.15/daprdocs/content/en/reference/components-reference/supported-state-stores/setup-oracledatabase.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
curl -X POST http://localhost:3500/v1.0/state \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"
  -d '[
        {
          "key": "temporary",
          "value": "ephemeral",
          "metadata": {"ttlInSeconds": "120"}}
        }
      ]'
```

